ASUS has showcased its NovaGo laptop at Mobile World Congress 2018. According to ASUS, the device is the world’s first gigabit LTE-capable laptop. The NovaGo is powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 835 chip, which features a X16 Gigabit LTE modem that supports download speeds “3-7 times faster than average broadband speeds”. Bluetooth 5 and 802.11ac Wi-Fi are also supported by the NovaGo laptop, and the device has a battery life of up to 22 hours. There is currently no availability information available for the ASUS NovaGo.